metadata.description:
Viviane Clay, Director of the Thousand Brains Project, presents the history of the Thousand Brains Project and the first implementation of the Thousand Brains Theory, Monty. 

00:00 Meet Monty 2026
01:21 What is the Thousand Brains Project?
02:43 The Legend of Monty
03:26 Vision
03:56 Guiding Principles
05:37 Learning Modules
05:52 Sensor Modules
06:11 Cortical Messaging Protocol
06:27 Evidence Based Learning Module
06:58 Intelligent Policies
07:19 Scaling
07:39 Optimization
07:48 Hierarchy
08:01 Real World Testing
08:41 Thousand Brains Project Announced
10:05 First Community Event
10:50 Thousand Brains Project Non-Profit Launched
11:52 tbp.floppy
12:06 Visualizations
12:28 Documentation
12:48 Compositional Models
13:57 Framework and Platform
14:36 Robot Hackathon
15:16 Ultrasound
16:08 Hypothesis Resampling
16:43 Model-Free Policies
17:04 Saliency
17:22 2D Sensor Module
17:36 Object Behaviors
18:12 Causal Interventions
18:24 Action Planning and Coordination
18:38 Attention
19:11 Research
20:24 Community Engagement
21:12 Looking Back

This presentation is part of our December, 2025 community meetup “Meet Monty 2026: Reverse Engineering Intelligence” playlist which you can view here: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLXpTU6oIscrkM2ZYSohq04cudo1cGGKTb
This two-hour playlist features nine short talks from the Thousand Brains Project team explaining various aspects of the project. Learn about Monty, a new type of AI, based on the principles of the neocortex. 

Get the code: https://github.com/thousandbrainsproject/tbp.monty
